body:
DT Fans United news

Okay, so I just talked to DT again, and now it’s pretty calm so I asked him about the book. I said we made him this book and sent it to him and just wondered if he got it.

He said he’s got a gigantic pile of fan mail in his house that he still needs to get to (it’s so big he’s ashamed to admit, sweet boy)… yeah. I said that we just wanted him to know that we put him and his family first, and that after he had to cancel the Chicago appearance last year, we were a bit worried and just wanted him to know we care. He was really touched by it (he really is the sweetest man on the planet) and he said that it’s very kind of us and he thanked me (us) ❤️

(If you’re worried, he did say it doesn’t mean he won’t get to it, it’s just that he’s a bit behind on things, that’s all. But he WILL get to it.)

summary: BBC America is going to help you get ready for Jodie Whittaker’s debut on ‘Doctor Who’.  The network will air a marathon of...
body:
Mega Doctor Who Marathon Coming To BBC America

BBC America is going to help you get ready for Jodie Whittaker’s debut on ‘Doctor Who’.  The network will air a marathon of every episode of the modern era of the show.   Beginning Tuesday, September 25th at 6am ET with ‘Rose’, the marathon will continue through the Eccleston, Tennant, Smith, and Capaldi years leading right to the premiere of ‘The Woman Who Fell to Earth’, Whittaker’s debut in the show on October 7th.  Fantastic!

summary: So happy I was able to go this year. And I finally met David Tennant today! My favorite Doctor Who. Couldn't think of a DW pose...
body:
Day 1 of #FanX18

So happy I was able to go this year. And I finally met David Tennant today! My favorite Doctor Who. Couldn’t think of a DW pose to save my life so I asked him for a hug and a bit of a forced smile. He was kinda confused until I said, “Yeah, ya know *slow creepy smile* smiiille.”

“Oooh, gotcha.”

Then of course I was so very happy to get to see Mark Sheppard again. He was just as sassy, witty, charming and a bit of a softy as always. When I got my photo op I asked if we could “look like we’re up to no good”. He looked at me and said, “Yeah, I bet you are.” I think I look more dorky than mischievous but still like how it turned out. (Pardon my face)
